HEADWORD: Running load
<hw>Run"ning load</hw>. <fld>(Aeronautics)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The
air pressure supported by each longitudinal foot segment of a
wing.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Commonly, the whole weight of aeroplane
and load divided by the span, or length from tip to tip.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Runningly</ent>⟦br⟧
